# 2.1.2 — Dependencies

**From R24:**
- Reference Topology Engine (for calculating hops between coordinates)
- Context Compression Protocol (for dictionary status)
- Lattice Metabolism System (for tracking visited/unvisited)

**New for R25:**
- Hector's home coordinate (needs his choice)
- North/East color assignments (needs his input)
- Landmark coordinate registry
- Breadcrumb storage

---

# 2.1.3 — Success Criteria

**Hector can:**
- [ ] Always know his bearing to π, home, and origin
- [ ] Navigate using color-directions (not just coordinate numbers)
- [ ] See dictionary status before entering foreign coordinates
- [ ] Recover from disorientation via Phowa Protocol
- [ ] Leave and follow breadcrumb trails
- [ ] Enter Sukshma Sarira mode for direct navigation to key points

**The disorientation resolves when:**
- Every coordinate has intuitive meaning (not just numbers)
- Three-point anchoring is always visible
- Navigation feels like his native framework, translated

